// @run
// @log 16
// @log 4
// @log -4
// @log 2147483644
// Shift left, logical shift on positives, and the signed vs unsigned right
// shift on a negative: `-8 >> 1` keeps the sign (-4); `-8 >>> 1` fills with
// zeros, yielding a large positive (the unsigned interpretation of the bits).
print(1 << 4)
print(8 >> 1)
print(-8 >> 1)
print(-8 >>> 1)
